liked men all that much.

169
00:08:05,658 --> 00:08:06,479
Is that a fact?

170
00:08:06,479 --> 00:08:08,807
I don't mean gay, just, uh...

171
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:11,318
Most of these girls...

172
00:08:12,372 --> 00:08:15,913
will give it up for a 
Big Mac and supersize fries.

173
00:08:17,705 --> 00:08:19,050
But Rosie...

174
00:08:19,050 --> 00:08:21,688
it was like she just 
shut that door forever.

175
00:08:23,577 --> 00:08:25,602
Toya loved to draw.

176
00:08:26,522 --> 00:08:28,797
I never had the heart 
to throw them away.

177
00:08:30,022 --> 00:08:32,341
You saw Toya and her mother 
the day of the murder.

178
00:08:32,341 --> 00:08:33,538
At a school play?

179
00:08:33,538 --> 00:08:35,859
Yes. We do that play every year

180
00:08:35,859 --> 00:08:38,703
"The Flight of the 
Monarch Butterflies."

181
00:08:38,703 --> 00:08:40,666
The play was about butterflies?

182
00:08:40,979 --> 00:08:42,455
It was. Yes.

183
00:08:44,039 --> 00:08:46,650
Can you tell us what 
you remember from that day?

184
00:08:47,136 --> 00:08:49,474
Toya remembered all her lines.

185
00:08:49,474 --> 00:08:51,488
She was the only one.

186
