200
00:09:41,583 --> 00:09:44,317
Two years is a long time to remember.

201
00:09:45,133 --> 00:09:47,594
Toya always came to school with a lunch.

202
00:09:47,594 --> 00:09:48,772
Clean clothes.

203
00:09:48,772 --> 00:09:50,427
She was a happy child.

204
00:09:50,427 --> 00:09:51,846
Loved.

205
00:09:52,243 --> 00:09:52,805
That's not something

206
00:09:52,805 --> 00:09:55,958
you forget either... 
not around here.

207
00:09:57,017 --> 00:09:58,088
So this is the bedroom

208
00:09:58,088 --> 00:09:59,522
where the murder took place?

209
00:09:59,522 --> 00:10:02,987
Yup. No renter since Rosie.

210
00:10:02,987 --> 00:10:04,943
Except my brother.

211
00:10:04,943 --> 00:10:07,380
Comes from Poland, stays here.

212
00:10:07,380 --> 00:10:11,276
God. Shut up, damn dogs. Be quiet!

213
00:10:11,276 --> 00:10:12,946
Hate those dogs.

214
00:10:14,713 --> 00:10:16,816
That wasn't in the crime scene photos.

215
00:10:16,816 --> 00:10:18,712
Maybe a cable line.

216
00:10:18,712 --> 00:10:19,994
Too big.

217
00:10:20,812 --> 00:10:22,345
And too high up.

218
00:10:23,696 --> 00:10:26,546
What happened to the bookshelf 
that was against this wall, Tammy?

219
00:10:26,546 --> 00:10:28,864
Oh. My place.

220
00:10:28,864 --> 00:10:29,582
Oh, yeah?

221
00:10:29,582 --> 00:10:30,322
Yeah.

222
00:10:30,322 --> 00:10:33,152
I keep it for Rosie. So what?

223
00:10:34,318 --> 00:10:36,252
Ever see any bruises on Toya?

224
00:10:36,252 --> 00:10:38,605
Bruises? No, no, no.

225
00:10:38,605 --> 00:10:40,152
Rosie never touch that girl.

226
00:10:40,152 --> 00:10:42,627
Never. Never. Uh-uh.

227
00:10:42,627 --> 00:10:45,020
Maybe one of her boyfriends did.

228
00:10:45,020 --> 00:10:46,092
Says here you saw someone

229
00:10:46,092 --> 00:10:47,564
running from the building that night.

230
00:10:47,564 --> 00:10:49,610
Yeah. Black.

231
00:10:49,610 --> 00:10:51,236
